{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[κίνημα]]''' (''kinema'') "movement", from '''[[κινέω]]''' (''kineo'') "to move, to put in motion".

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-both}}

# {{cattag|countable}} a [[film]]
# {{cattag|countable}} a [[movie]] [[theatre]]
#: ''The '''cinema''' is right across the street from the restaurant.''
# {{cattag|filmology|uncountable}} film or movies as a [[group]]
#: ''Despite the critics, he produced excellent '''cinema'''.''
# {{cattag|filmology|uncountable}} the film and movie [[industry]]
#: ''In the long history of Spanish '''cinema'''....''
# {{cattag|filmology|uncountable}} the [[art]] of making films and movies
#: ''Throughout the history of '''cinema''', filmmakers....''

